The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 ICC seeks IOC membership

New Delhi: Cricket in Olympics could be a reality with the ICC seeking membership of the International Olympic Council (IOC) to include the Twenty20 format in the biggest sporting extravaganza on earth. 

ICC chief executive Malcolm Speed said the abridged format is best suited for the Olympics considering the nature of the games and ICC was in the process of getting IOC membership. 

